#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.103"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.103:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.103:0.2"
msgid "11. Phāsuvihāravagga"
msgstr "11. Living Comfortably"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.103:0.3"
msgid "103. Mahācorasutta"
msgstr "103. A Master Thief"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato mahācoro sandhimpi chindati, "
"nillopampi harati, ekāgārikampi karoti, paripanthepi tiṭṭhati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a master thief with five factors breaks into houses, plunders "
"wealth, steals from isolated buildings, and commits highway robbery."

msgctxt "an5.103:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.103:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito ca hoti, gahananissito ca, "
"balavanissito ca, bhogacāgī ca, ekacārī ca."
msgstr ""
"A master thief relies on rough ground, on thick cover, and on powerful "
"individuals; they pay bribes, and they act alone."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a master thief rely on rough ground?"

msgctxt "an5.103:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro nadīviduggaṃ vā nissito hoti pabbatavisamaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a master thief relies on inaccessible riverlands or rugged "
"mountains."

msgctxt "an5.103:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a master thief relies on rough ground."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro gahananissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a master thief rely on thick cover?"

#. VAR: rodhaṃ → gedhaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.103:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro tiṇagahanaṃ vā nissito hoti rukkhagahanaṃ vā "
"rodhaṃ vā mahāvanasaṇḍaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a master thief relies on thick grass, thick trees, a ridge, or a "
"large dense wood."

msgctxt "an5.103:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro gahananissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a master thief relies on thick cover."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.129"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro balavanissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a master thief rely on powerful individuals?"

msgctxt "an5.103:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro rājānaṃ vā rājamahāmattānaṃ vā nissito hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a master thief relies on rulers or their ministers."

msgctxt "an5.103:4.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an5.103:4.4"
msgid ""
"‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ime me rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya "
"atthaṃ bhaṇissantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If anyone accuses me of anything, these rulers or their ministers will "
"speak in my defense in the case.’"

msgctxt "an5.103:4.5"
msgid ""
"Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tyassa rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya "
"atthaṃ bhaṇanti."
msgstr "And that’s exactly what happens."

msgctxt "an5.103:4.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro balavanissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a master thief relies on powerful individuals."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro bhogacāgī hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a master thief pay bribes?"

msgctxt "an5.103:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro aḍḍho hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo."
msgstr "It’s when a master thief is rich, affluent, and wealthy."

msgctxt "an5.103:5.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an5.103:5.4"
msgid "‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ito bhogena paṭisantharissāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘If anyone accuses me of anything, I’ll settle it with a bribe.’"

msgctxt "an5.103:5.5"
msgid "Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tato bhogena paṭisantharati."
msgstr "And that’s exactly what happens."

msgctxt "an5.103:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro bhogacāgī hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a master thief pays bribes."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro ekacārī hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a master thief act alone?"

#. VAR: gahaṇāni → niggahaṇāni (bj, s1-3, km) | niggahanāni (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.103:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro ekakova gahaṇāni kattā hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a master thief carries out robbery all alone."

msgctxt "an5.103:6.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an5.103:6.4"
msgid "‘Mā me guyhamantā bahiddhā sambhedaṃ agamaṃsū’ti."
msgstr "So that their secret plans are not leaked to others."

msgctxt "an5.103:6.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro ekacārī hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a master thief acts alone."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:7.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato mahācoro sandhimpi chindati "
"nillopampi harati ekāgārikampi karoti paripanthepi tiṭṭhati."
msgstr ""
"A master thief with these five factors breaks into houses, plunders wealth, "
"steals from isolated buildings, and commits highway robbery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:8.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato pāpabhikkhu khataṃ "
"upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca "
"apuññaṃ pasavati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a bad mendicant has five factors, they keep themselves "
"broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible "
"people, and they make much bad karma."

msgctxt "an5.103:8.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.103:8.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito ca hoti, gahananissito ca, "
"balavanissito ca, bhogacāgī ca, ekacārī ca."
msgstr ""
"A bad mendicant relies on rough ground, on thick cover, and on powerful "
"individuals; they pay bribes, and they act alone."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a bad mendicant rely on rough ground?"

msgctxt "an5.103:9.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamena kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, visamena "
"vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, visamena manokammena samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a bad mendicant has unethical conduct by way of body, speech, and "
"mind."

msgctxt "an5.103:9.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a bad mendicant relies on rough ground."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.130"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:10.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu gahananissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a bad mendicant rely on thick cover?"

msgctxt "an5.103:10.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu micchādiṭṭhiko hoti antaggāhikāya diṭṭhiyā "
"samannāgato."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a bad mendicant has wrong view, he’s attached to an extremist view."

msgctxt "an5.103:10.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu gahananissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a bad mendicant relies on thick cover."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:11.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu balavanissito hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a bad mendicant rely on powerful individuals?"

msgctxt "an5.103:11.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu rājānaṃ vā rājamahāmattānaṃ vā nissito hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a bad mendicant relies on rulers or their ministers."

msgctxt "an5.103:11.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an5.103:11.4"
msgid ""
"‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ime me rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya "
"atthaṃ bhaṇissantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If anyone accuses me of anything, these rulers or their ministers will "
"speak in my defense in the case.’"

msgctxt "an5.103:11.5"
msgid ""
"Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tyassa rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya "
"atthaṃ bhaṇanti."
msgstr "And that’s exactly what happens."

msgctxt "an5.103:11.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu balavanissito hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a bad mendicant relies on powerful individuals."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:12.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu bhogacāgī hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a bad mendicant pay bribes?"

msgctxt "an5.103:12.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu lābhī hoti "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a bad mendicant receives robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines "
"and supplies for the sick."

msgctxt "an5.103:12.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an5.103:12.4"
msgid "‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ito lābhena paṭisantharissāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘If anyone accuses me of anything, I’ll settle it with a bribe.’"

msgctxt "an5.103:12.5"
msgid "Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tato lābhena paṭisantharati."
msgstr "And that’s exactly what happens."

msgctxt "an5.103:12.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu bhogacāgī hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a bad mendicant pays bribes."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:13.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu ekacārī hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a bad mendicant act alone?"

msgctxt "an5.103:13.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu ekakova paccantimesu janapadesu nivāsaṃ kappeti."
msgstr "It’s when a bad mendicant dwells alone in the borderlands."

msgctxt "an5.103:13.3"
msgid "So tattha kulāni upasaṅkamanto lābhaṃ labhati."
msgstr "They visit families there to get material possessions."

msgctxt "an5.103:13.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu ekacārī hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a bad mendicant acts alone."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an5.103:14.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato pāpabhikkhu khataṃ "
"upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca "
"apuññaṃ pasavatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a bad mendicant has these five factors, they keep themselves broken and "
"damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and "
"they make much bad karma.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.103:14.2"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
